Night Sky by Clare Francis EPUB

Night Sky is Clare Francis' sweeping chronicle of Europe in peace and war, a tremendous floodtide of narrative that builds to a gripping and unforgettable finale.

In the brutal chaos of the Second World War, three people find their lives inextricably interwoven in a web of courage, betrayal, and love: Julie Lescaux, the young Englishwoman caught up in one of the most dangerous operations of the French Resistance; Paul Vasson, vicious Paris Pimp turned Nazi collaborator; and David Freymann, German scientist caught up in an unimaginable horror, destined to lose everything except his faith in his own discovery.
